Tabs definned in OmopViewer

supported_result_type.Rmd

The OmopViewer package generates shiny apps from predefined configurations, you can check the existent panels using the defaultPanels() function:

defaultPanels()
#>  [1] "incidence"                               
#>  [2] "incidence_attrition"                     
#>  [3] "prevalence"                              
#>  [4] "prevalence_attrition"                    
#>  [5] "summarise_cohort_overlap"                
#>  [6] "summarise_cohort_count"                  
#>  [7] "summarise_cohort_attrition"              
#>  [8] "summarise_cohort_timing"                 
#>  [9] "summarise_characteristics"               
#> [10] "summarise_omop_snapshot"                 
#> [11] "summarise_observation_period"            
#> [12] "summarise_clinical_records"              
#> [13] "summarise_record_count"                  
#> [14] "summarise_missing_data"                  
#> [15] "summarise_in_observation"                
#> [16] "orphan_code_use"                         
#> [17] "cohort_code_use"                         
#> [18] "code_use"                                
#> [19] "achilles_code_use"                       
#> [20] "unmpaped_codes"                          
#> [21] "summarise_dose_coverage"                 
#> [22] "summarise_proportion_of_patients_covered"
#> [23] "summarise_drug_restart"                  
#> [24] "summarise_drug_utilisation"              
#> [25] "summarise_indication"                    
#> [26] "summarise_treatment"                     
#> [27] "default"

You can check the details of a panel using getPanel() function:

getPanel("incidence")
#> Incidence (OmopViewer panel)
#> • icon: chart-line
#> • data: result_type: <incidence>
#> • filters: 1 filters + 6 automatic filters
#> • content: Tidy (DT); Table Incidence (gt); Plot Incidence (plot)

The exported object omopViewerPanels contains all the defined panels in the package:

omopViewerPanels
#> $incidence
#> Incidence (OmopViewer panel)
#> • icon: chart-line
#> • data: result_type: <incidence>
#> • filters: 1 filters + 6 automatic filters
#> • content: Tidy (DT); Table Incidence (gt); Plot Incidence (plot)
#> 
#> $incidence_attrition
#> Incidence Attrition (OmopViewer panel)
#> • icon: layer-group

Note for developers

If you wish to configure a new Tab this can be done editing the omopViewerPanels object defined in in file panels.R. Please feel free to submit your PR.
